The paper focuses on using fitness landscapes to study the performance of neuroevolution, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI). The study specifically uses a grammar-based approach to generate convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization power and generalization ability of the method, which are relevant to control systems and robotics (cs.SY).
